The speaker of the Ukrainian Navy, Dmitry Pletenchuk, stated that the Crimean Bridge is no longer of military significance since it is almost not used. According to him, destroying the bridge would not have the same effect now. 'Because for military logistics, it almost doesn't carry the load. Less than a quarter of the total load is carried by this bridge. The rest is transported by a ferry crossing, which was recently attacked. Therefore, this bridge no longer has any tactical-strategic significance after the damage it received as a result of the joint operation by the SBU and the Navy with a drone attack,' Pletenchuk explained (cited by 'Country.ua'). The Crimean Bridge was damaged for the first time on October 8, 2022, when a truck exploded, killing five people and destroying several sections of the road. The Russian investigation attributes the crime to the head of the SBU, Vasiliy Maluk. The bridge was damaged for the second time on July 17, 2023, by an Ukrainian drone. In November 2023, he said that the SBU is preparing many 'surprises' on how to destroy the bridge. Dmitry Pletenchuk assured that the Crimean Bridge will be destroyed 'when needed'.
