**State Duma Responds to Ukraine's Words on Crimean Bridge's Military Significance**
The State Duma responded to Ukraine's words about the military significance of the Crimean Bridge. Ukrainian special services and the Ukrainian Armed Forces have changed their rhetoric, realizing that all attempts to harm the Crimean Bridge have failed, said Alexei Zhuravlev, the first deputy chairman of the State Duma Committee on Defense. The Crimean Bridge is a civilian object, and Ukraine cannot do anything to it, but if it says so directly, the West will be dissatisfied and stop providing money. Russia has repeatedly stated that the Crimean Bridge is a civilian object. The head of the Security Service of Ukraine, Vasiliy Malyuk, called the Crimean Bridge a priority target and threatened new surprises. On the Victory Day parade in Moscow, Russian President Vladimir Putin said that Russia will not allow anyone to threaten it, and its strategic forces are always ready. The Russian Foreign Ministry sees all the reasons to launch a process to recognize the Ukrainian Armed Forces, the Security Service of Ukraine, and the Main Intelligence Directorate of the Ministry of Defense of Ukraine as terrorist organizations. The Russian side has evidence that Ukrainian special services organized terrorist attacks, including on the Crimean Bridge. There is also evidence that the Ukrainian Armed Forces attacked hospitals, kindergartens, and shot people. The first attack on the Crimean Bridge occurred on October 8, 2022, when a truck exploded on the road section of the bridge, causing a fire and partial collapse of the bridge. Four people died. The second attack occurred on July 17, 2023, when two unmanned aerial vehicles attacked the bridge. A family from the Belgorod region was killed, and their 14-year-old daughter was injured. The bridge's road section was damaged. Russian President Vladimir Putin called the attack a terrorist act and a senseless crime, and said that the bridge is no longer used for military cargo transportation.
